<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[130,776,216,624]" box="[132,232,216,242]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[130,776,216,624]" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">
With the kind assistance of Herbarium staff at BM Lindley’s original material was located. This specimen bears flowers and may have provided the basis for the illustration of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Photinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Photinia dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="LINDLEY J." box="[228,392,343,370]" firstAuthor="Lindley" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Linnean Society of London Botany" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="88 - 106" part="13" refId="ref3737" refString="LINDLEY J. 1821. - Observation on the natural group of plants called Pomaceae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London Botany 13: 88 - 106. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1821. tb 00058. x" title="Observation on the natural group of plants called Pomaceae" type="journal article" year="1821">Lindley (1821)</bibRefCitation>
, and consequently this sheet would make a suitable lectotype. Hence, following ICN Art. 9.3, 9.12 (
<bibRefCitation author="TURLAND N. J. &amp; WIERSEMA J. H. &amp; BARRIE F. R. &amp; GREUTER W. &amp; HAWKSWORTH D. &amp; HERENDEEN P. S. &amp; KNAPP S. &amp; KUSBER W. H. &amp; LI D. - Z. &amp; MARHOLD K. &amp; MAY T. W. &amp; MCNEILL J. &amp; MONRO A. M. &amp; PRADO J. &amp; PRICE M. J. &amp; SMITH G. F." bookContentInfo="254 p." box="[201,417,407,433]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Turland" journalOrPublisher="Regnum Vegetabile" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" part="159" refId="ref4207" refString="TURLAND N. J., WIERSEMA J. H., BARRIE F. R., GREUTER W., HAWKSWORTH D., HERENDEEN P. S., KNAPP S., KUSBER W. H., LI D. - Z., MARHOLD K., MAY T. W., MCNEILL J., MONRO A. M., PRADO J., PRICE M. J. &amp; SMITH G. F. (eds). 2018. - International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 254 p. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[297,351,407,433]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), we here designate the original specimen deposited atBM013717909 as lectotype, superseding 
<bibRefCitation author="VIDAL J. E." box="[172,311,471,498]" firstAuthor="Vidal" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia, nouvelle serie" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="537 - 580" part="5" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/59879883" refId="ref4352" refString="VIDAL J. E. 1965. - Notes sur quelques Rosacees asiatiques (III). Revision du genre Eriobotrya (Pomoideae). Adansonia, nouvelle serie 5: 537 - 580. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 59879883" title="Notes sur quelques Rosacees asiatiques (III). Revision du genre Eriobotrya (Pomoideae)" type="journal article" year="1965">Vidal (1965)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="LIU B. B. &amp; LIU G. N. &amp; HONG D. Y. &amp; WEN J." box="[368,552,471,497]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Liu" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="99 - 118" part="139" refId="ref3864" refString="LIU B. B., LIU G. N., HONG D. Y. &amp; WEN J. 2020 a. - Typification of 23 names in Eriobotrya (Maleae, Rosaceae). PhytoKeys 139: 99 - 118. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / phytokeys. 139.47967" title="Typification of 23 names in Eriobotrya (Maleae, Rosaceae)" type="journal article" year="2020" yearSuffix="a">
Liu 
<emphasis box="[412,462,471,497]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
(2020a)
</bibRefCitation>
selection of “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">Wallich 668.1”</emphasis>
as provided by ICN Art. 9.19 (
<bibRefCitation author="TURLAND N. J. &amp; WIERSEMA J. H. &amp; BARRIE F. R. &amp; GREUTER W. &amp; HAWKSWORTH D. &amp; HERENDEEN P. S. &amp; KNAPP S. &amp; KUSBER W. H. &amp; LI D. - Z. &amp; MARHOLD K. &amp; MAY T. W. &amp; MCNEILL J. &amp; MONRO A. M. &amp; PRADO J. &amp; PRICE M. J. &amp; SMITH G. F." bookContentInfo="254 p." box="[551,759,503,529]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Turland" journalOrPublisher="Regnum Vegetabile" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" part="159" refId="ref4207" refString="TURLAND N. J., WIERSEMA J. H., BARRIE F. R., GREUTER W., HAWKSWORTH D., HERENDEEN P. S., KNAPP S., KUSBER W. H., LI D. - Z., MARHOLD K., MAY T. W., MCNEILL J., MONRO A. M., PRADO J., PRICE M. J. &amp; SMITH G. F. (eds). 2018. - International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 254 p. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis box="[644,696,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). The selected sheet is a complete and well-preserved specimen that displays morphological diagnostic traits in agreement with the protologue.
</paragraph>
